ticipate in this as well.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Q: Why not use richer architectures for experiments?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A: Since there are already many components in the proposed agent, to isolate possible factors that would influence the agent behaviors, we use the minimal architecture sizes that marginally enables good RL performance on our test settings.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Q: Why not use MCTS as the search method for decision-time planning?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A: Unlike AlphaGo, which employs MCTS, our architecture is based on the simplest baseline DQN. DQN uses a value-estimator based greedy policy instead of a parameterized one as the actor-critic architecture used in AlphaGo. The DQN policy is deterministic <em>w.r.t.</em> the estimated values therefore the planning cannot take sufficient advantage of the sample based MCTS.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":233,\"width\":610,\"height\":565,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"http://localhost/homepage/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/image-1.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-233\" width=\"610\" height=\"565\"/><figcaption><em>A birdseye view of the overall design</em></figcaption></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'A Step Towards Conscious Planning', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '205-revision-v1', '', '', '2021-09-15 10:50:00', '2021-09-15 14:50:00', '', 205, 'http://localhost/homepage/?p=288', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(295, 1, '2021-09-25 22:38:54', '2021-09-26 02:38:54', '<!-- wp:group {\"align\":\"wide\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group alignwide\"><!-- wp:columns -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\"><!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:block {\"ref\":197} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Page Last Updated: 15 Sep. 2021</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:media-text {\"mediaPosition\":\"right\",\"mediaId\":71,\"mediaType\":\"image\",\"mediaWidth\":23,\"mediaSizeSlug\":\"full\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-media-text alignwide has-media-on-the-right is-stacked-on-mobile\" style=\"grid-template-columns:auto 23%\"><figure class=\"wp-block-media-text__media\"><img src=\"http://localhost/homepage/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/logo_MILA-180x180-1.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-71 size-full\"/></figure><div class=\"wp-block-media-text__content\"><!-- wp:paragraph {\"placeholder\":\"Content…\",\"fontSize\":\"small\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-small-font-size\">I am a researcher at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://mila.quebec/en/\">Mila</a>&nbsp;(Quebec AI Institute) interested in the learning aspects of AI, especially Reinforcement Learning (RL).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:media-text -->\n\n<!-- wp:media-text {\"mediaPosition\":\"right\",\"mediaId\":72,\"mediaLink\":\"http://localhost/homepage/the-new-umoma-opens-its-doors-2/mcgill-bird/\",\"mediaType\":\"image\",\"mediaWidth\":23,\"mediaSizeSlug\":\"full\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-media-text alignwide has-media-on-the-right is-stacked-on-mobile\" style=\"grid-template-columns:auto 23%\"><figure class=\"wp-block-media-text__media\"><img src=\"http://localhost/homepage/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/McGill-Bird-1024x1024.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-72 size-full\"/></figure><div class=\"wp-block-media-text__content\"><!-- wp:paragraph {\"placeholder\":\"Content…\",\"fontSize\":\"small\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-sma